Key Match Events: Philadelphia Phillies' comeback in the sixth inning leading to a three-run home run by Brandon Marsh; Nick Castellanos hitting a go-ahead two-run homer in the seventh inning
Post-Match Reflections: The win improved the Philadelphia Phillies' record to 79-55, six games ahead of Atlanta in the NL East standings
Miscellaneous Highlights: The series opener was the first of a four-game series; the next game featured a potential pitching duel between Reynaldo Lopez and Ranger Suarez
